<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_72.HTM#Sec4>


Bluetongue in Israel

(Date of previous outbreak of bluetongue in Israel reported to the OIE:
December 2001).

Extract from the monthly report of Israel for September 2003, received on 6
Nov 2003 from Dr Oded Nir, Director of Veterinary and Animal Health
Services, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, Beit Dagan:

Location No. of outbreaks in September 2003
Gan-Hashomron, Hadera district 1

Total number of animals in the outbreak:

species / susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
ovi / 100 / 17 / 0 / 0 / 0

Note by the OIE Animal Health Information Department:

- The monthly report referred to above is a corrected version of the
original report submitted to the OIE Headquarters, in which bluetongue was
reported absent in September 2003.

- The monthly report of Israel for October 2003 reports the absence of any
new outbreaks of bluetongue.

Animal Health Information Department
Office international des Epizooties (OIE)
<information.dept@oie.int>

